    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-19T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-19T16:30:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <head>479. Memorandum of a Telephone Conversation Between the Secretary of State and
                    the Director of Central Intelligence (<persName corresp="#p_DAW1"
                        >Dulles</persName>), Washington, July 19, 1956, 5:30 p.m.<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d479fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library, Dulles Papers,
                        General Telephone Conversations. Transcribed by <persName corresp="#p_AM1"
                            >Asbjornson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1956-07-19T17:30:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1956, 5:30 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_Sec1">Sec</gloss>. called and said he had just finished his
                    talk with the Egyptian Amb.,<note n="2" xml:id="d479fn2">See <ref target="#d478">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> who had handled himself surprisingly well and with dignity. The
                    Secretary read AWD the statement and the latter thought it was a good one.</p>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_Sec1">Sec</gloss>. gave a précis of what he had told
                        <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName>.</p>
                <pb facs="0902" n="874" xml:id="pg_874"/>
                <p>AWD said he would like some copies of the press release on the Aswan Dam as soon
                    as he could have them so he could have it for his purposes, (cjp<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d479fn3">Carolyn J. Proctor.</note> is handling)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
